why are drug interventions needed by some addicts there are already lots of drug rehabilitation programs that proliferate our society today why is it that there are people who are drug dependent who still need drug interventions what does an intervention do anyway there are a lot of drug dependent individuals who find it hard to accept that they have a problem regarding their intake of drugs this is one main obstacle that they have to overcome a drug intervention is done to make these people realize that they have a problem regarding their substance abuse and thus help them to accept that they have to get themselves treated for their condition Drug addiction Addiction Alcoholism Substance abuse Controlled Substances Act Single Convention on Narcotic Drugs Diazepam Medicine Arguments for and against drug prohibition Folic acid Clinical depression Narcotic Cancer Convention on Psychotropic Substances Schizophrenia Illegal drug trade Methamphetamine Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Withdrawal Drug test Chlorpromazine Opioid Anorexia nervosa Haloperidol Clomipramine Psychiatry Bipolar disorder Health care in the United States War on Drugs Borderline personality disorder Anxiety Multiple sclerosis Antiretroviral drug Traditional Chinese medicine Sexual addiction Obesity Insulin Methylphenidate LSD Doxepin Pharmaceutical company Psychosis Traumatic brain injury Prohibition (drugs) Paracetamol National Institutes of Health Lorazepam Recreational drug use Hypoglycemia Cocaine Homelessness Anti-psychiatry A Scanner Darkly Psychopharmacology Health insurance Soft drug Rat Park Buprenorphine Prostate cancer Controversies in autism Veganism Adult attention-deficit disorder Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Narcissism Abortion Procrastination Hearing impairment Criticism of libertarianism Obsessive-compulsive disorder Bradley Nowell Consensual crime Drug policy of the Netherlands Barbiturate Caffeine AIDS Medical cannabis Insomnia Maprotiline Alcoholics Anonymous Mental illness Epi